content.description: Starting on a sloping pseudo-crimp sidepull with the right hand, a crimp on the left, and the tip of a flake for a foot off to the right, use the two cracks running up the left side of the boulder. Top out roughly over where you started. Precision foot placement is key and balance is essential for this route. Can be a frustrating line to project, but is rewarding when you finish it.
content.protection: Two pads are all that is needed, but are placed over a large steep rock, making for scary falls where you can easily slip on the pads. A spotter may be nice to keep falling down hill and not landing directly on the rocks.
content.location: On the boulder just to the right of Premium Coffee when you walk up the trail from the road. It's the leftmost problem on this boulder.

content.description: This little guy was a 2-3 move wonder. Big grippy holds on the right face lead up the seam to a sloping lip before a mondo jug. More campus then anything, not very unique movement.
content.location: Right behind the Unobvious Boulder on the left. The problem is facing South East(ish), same direction of Premium Coffee. Standing start on the right side on the 2 big slopers.

content.description: Sit start using opposing side pulls, then using the seams and crimps climb straight up and top out. Felt harder than unobvious but equally worth doing.
This is the obvious line of fine grained slopers trending up and left from the starting sloper.  Eventually get your foot on the starting hold and rock up to the jug.
content.location: This is on the first boulder encountered as you enter the woods on the north side of the highway.  Start sitting with both hands matched on the lowest sloper, and a big but slopey foothold.

content.description: Climb the right juggy arete of the Premium Coffee boulder. It's listed as a V1 in the Sheridan guide book, but its probably the easiest "V1" I've ever done. The landing is bad, but that's really it.
content.protection: 1.5 pad and a spotter. The 0.5 pad is for the stump.
content.location: The arete to the right of Premium Coffee on the little incline with a tree stump.

content.description: Left of the tree, climb a bulge to a left-facing flake, then mantle right under a tree branch.
content.protection: 1 pad and a spotter if you're not confident you'll flash it. Might hit the tree on the way down.
content.location: It's the first climb on the right in the Premium Coffee area, right next to Unobvious V3
